r antibodies?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Immunofluorescence microscopy","Immunonephelometry","Protein electrophoresis","Enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay","Western blot"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eenzyme-linked immunosorbent assay\u003C/strong\u003E (ELISA) is the most widely used immunological test due to its high sensitivity, specificity, and ability to process multiple samples simultaneously. It can be automated and provides quantitative results at relatively low cost.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other techniques have specific limitations:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmunofluorescence microscopy\u003C/strong\u003E requires specialized equipment and is labour-intensive\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmunonephelometry\u003C/strong\u003E measures scattered light from antigen-antibody complexes but has limited applications\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProtein electrophoresis\u003C/strong\u003E separates proteins by charge but cannot identify specific antigens or antibodies\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWestern blot\u003C/strong\u003E provides high specificity but is more complex, time-consuming and expensive than ELISA\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EELISA has become the standard method for detecting and quantifying specific proteins, hormones, and other molecules in biological samples due to its practical advantages and reliable results.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) is the gold standard laboratory technique for detecting and quantifying specific antigens or antibodies","ELISA offers advantages of high sensitivity, specificity, automation capability, and cost-effectiveness compared to other immunological tests","ELISA allows simultaneous processing of multiple samples and provides quantitative results"],"references":["K